This is zntpdate for SCO, *nux, *bsd, Mac OS X

Contents:
	zntpdate tool to update date/time with offset options and
	European Summer Time feature.

Requires:
	Working compiler, libc and socket lib.

Installation:
	Do "./configure --help" and decide what options you want. The
	default should be suitable for most SCO and Linux systems.
	Then run the configure script.

	Do "make" to compile zntpdate.
	Then (as root) do "make install".

Jean-Michel Marino
